OL,3,CPM 'talking to chief constable about
OL,4,Cpossible' PSNI support
OL,6,F"The chief constable recently wrote to
OL,7,Fthe Prime Minister, requesting
OL,8,Fadditional budgetary support to
OL,9,Fimplement his plan for better policing
OL,10,Fin Northern Ireland.
OL,12,F"This is not a bid for attention, but
OL,13,Fa serious effort to ensure the PSNI is
OL,14,Fequipped to fulfill its statutory
OL,15,Fobligations, including protecting life
OL,16,Fand property, maintaining law and
OL,17,Forder, and preventing crime.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/5
